==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Picnic
<hw>Pic"nic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>piquenique</ets>. See <er>Pick</er>, <pos>v.</pos>, and cf.
<er>Knickknack</er>.]</ety> <def>Formerly, an entertainment at which
each person contributed some dish to a common table; now, an excursion
or pleasure party in which the members partake of a collation or repast
(usually in the open air, and from food carried by
themselves).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Picnic</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Picnic
<hw>Pic"nic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Picnicked</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Picnicking</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <def>To go on
a picnic, or pleasure excursion; to eat in public fashion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Picnicker</ent>⟦br⟧
